5 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Construction. (1) [Sections 1 through 4] must be construed in favor of a
6 broad protection of free exercise of religious beliefs to the maximum extent permitted by the state and federal
7 constitutions.
8 (2) The protection of free exercise of religious beliefs afforded by [sections 1 through 4] are in
9 addition to the protections provided under federal law, state law, and the state and federal constitutions.
10 Nothing in [sections 1 through 4] may be construed to:
11 (a) preempt or repeal any state or local law that is equally or more protective of free exercise of
12 religious beliefs;
13 (b) narrow the meaning or application of any state or local law protecting free exercise of religious
14 beliefs; or
15 (c) prevent the state government from providing, either directly or through an individual or entity
16 not seeking protection under [sections 1 through 4] any benefit or service authorized under state law.
17
18 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Codification instruction. [Sections 1 through 4] are intended to be
19 codified as a new part in Title 42, chapter 7, and the provisions of Title 42, chapter 7, apply to [sections 1
20 through 4].
21
22 NEW SECTION. Section 6. Severability. If a part of [this act] is invalid, all valid parts that are
23 severable from the invalid part remain in effect. If a part of [this act] is invalid in one or more of its applications,
24 the part remains in effect in all valid applications that are severable from the invalid applications.
